<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-56-0153 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper describes BIO-JOULE, a bimonthly newsletter (circulation over4,000), which reports on the significant events, developments, contracts,trends, conferences, public and private sector hopes and concerns, significantpublications, environmental, economic, ecological, technological andsocietal implications of emergent bioenergy technology and implementation.To achieve this the Biomass Energy Institute receives and scans over100 energy and biomass-related periodicals plus numerous proceedingsof relevant conferences in renewable energy and energy conservation.Correspondence is maintained with the energy sector in Canada, U.S.A.and over 50 other coutries. The Institute's policies forbid it to adopta doctrinaire position on any form of energy.</TEXT></DOC>